{"lemma":"حَرَدِ","slug":"حَرَدِ","root":"ح.ر.د","root_slug":"ح-ر-د","root_link":"/words/roots/ح-ر-د","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"حَرَدِ","root":"حرد","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":false},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n7589","n7590","n7593","n7594","n7595","n7596"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AD%D9%8E%D8%B1%D9%8E%D8%AF%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":null,"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n7589","headword_ar":"حَرَدَ","root":"Hrd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A, Msb, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HarodN","text_ar":"حَرْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He tended, repaired, betook himself,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"directed himself"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his course"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"aim, to"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"towards; made for"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"towards; aimed at; sought, pursued, desired,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"intended;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(him, or it; IAar, K;) syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaSada","text_ar":"قَصَدَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (IAar, S, A, Msb, K.) Agreeably with this explanation, some render the"},{"kind":"page_break","n":544},{"kind":"text","text":"words of the Kur [lxviii. 25],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wagadawoA EalaY HarodK","text_ar":"وَغَدَوْا عَلَى حَرْدٍ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaAdiriyna","text_ar":"قَادِرِينَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S.) You say to a man, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qado Haradotu Harodaka","text_ar":"قَدْ حَرَدْتُ حَرْدَكَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I have tended, repaired,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"towards, thee;"},{"kind":"text","text":"like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaSadotu qaSodaka","text_ar":"قَصَدْتُ قَصْدَكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Fr, S, * L) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aqobalotu qibalaka","text_ar":"اَقْبَلْتُ قِبَلَكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Fr, L.) A rájiz says, (S,) namely, Hassán, (so in a copy of the S,)"},{"kind":"quote","text":"A^aqobala sayolN jaA='a mino A^amori A@ll~`ha\n                      \n                     \n                        yaHoridu Haroda Aljan~api Almugil~aho"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A torrent advanced, that came by the command of God, tending to the fruitful garden"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S.)       -A2-  Also, aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HarodN","text_ar":"حَرْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, L,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He prevented, hindered, impeded, withheld, restrained, debarred, inhibited, forbade, prohibited,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"interdicted;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, S, K;) and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hr~d","text_ar":"حرّد","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (L, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taHoriydN","text_ar":"تَحْرِيدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) Agreeably with this explanation, also, some render the words of the Kur cited above: from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAradato","text_ar":"حَارَدَتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"said of she-camels, meaning “ they became scanty in their supplies of milk. ” (S.)       -A3-  Also, aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, L, K,) or"},{"kind":"text","text":", (AZ, S, L,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HuruwdN","text_ar":"حُرُودٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, K;) [and app. ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tHr~d","text_ar":"تحرّد","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AnHrd","text_ar":"انحرد","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HariydN","text_ar":"حَرِيدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":";)]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a man)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"separated himself from others;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he left,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abandoned,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"forsook, his people, and removed from them;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AZ, S;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he retired from his people, and alighted,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"took up his abode, in a place by himself."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.)       -A4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Harida","text_ar":"حَرِدَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Sb, S, Msb, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Harada","text_ar":"حَرَدَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (L, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HarodN","text_ar":"حَرْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Sb, As, T, IDrd, S, Msb, &c.,) so says Aboo-Nasr Ahmad Ibn-Hátim, companion of As, (S,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaradN","text_ar":"حَرَدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, S, Msb,) this latter form of the inf. n. sometimes used, accord. to ISk, (S,) and this is the form heard by AZ and AO and As from the Arabs of chaste speech, (TA,) but both forms are chaste, (IAar, TA,) though the former is the more common, (IAar, Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, angry:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K, &c.:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, exasperated"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tHr~$","text_ar":"تحرّش"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by one who angered him, and desired to kill him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, L.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Harada Ealayohi","text_ar":"حَرَدَ عَلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, L) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Harida","text_ar":"حَرِدَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was angry with him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, L.)       -A5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Harida","text_ar":"حَرِدَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaradN","text_ar":"حَرَدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Mgh, Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a camel)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"had the disease termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaradN","text_ar":"حَرَدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]: (K:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he had the tendons,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sinews, of one of his fore legs relaxed by the cord whereby the fore shank is sometimes bound up to the arm,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"had them in that state naturally,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, Msb, *)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"so that he shook his fore legs,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"so that he beat the ground"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with the fore leg"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (Mgh, Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in walking,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"going:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, Msb:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a camel)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"had the tendon,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sinew, of his arm broken, so that his fore leg became lax, and he never ceased to shake it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"the tendon, or sinew, breaks only in the outer side of the arm, and it [the arm] seems, when the camel walks or is in motion, as though it stretched, by reason of his raising it so high from the ground, and by reason of its laxness: (ISh, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a beast)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"raised his legs very high, in walking,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"going, and put them down in their place, by reason of his being very short in his step."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.) ―         -b2-  Also, aor. and inf. n. as above,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a man)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was oppressed by the weight of his coat of mail, so that he was unable to stretch himself out in walking."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b3-  And, with the same aor. and inf. n.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a bowstring)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"had one or more of the several portions of which"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by their being twisted together"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it was composed longer than others."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.)"}],"source_refs":["S","A","Msb","K","L","AZ","Sb","T","TA","IAar","Mgh","ISh"]},{"entry_id":"n7590","headword_ar":"حرّد","root":"Hrd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see 1.       -A2-  Also, (T, L, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taHoriydN","text_ar":"تَحْرِيدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He twisted"},{"kind":"text","text":"a rope"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"so tightly that the strands formed knots, and overlay one another:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, L:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he rolled"},{"kind":"text","text":"a rope"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in twisting it"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^adoraja fatolahu","text_ar":"اَدْرَجَ فَتْلَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"so that it became round."},{"kind":"text","text":"(AHn, L, K.) [See also the pass. part. n., below.] ―         -b2-  And, (K,) inf. n. as above, (S, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He crooked, curved,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"a thing, (S, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the form of an arch."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) ―         -b3-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HurodiYN","text_ar":"حُرْدِىٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". [It seems to be implied in the L, that one says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hr~d HaAy^iTa AlqaSabi","text_ar":"حرّد حَايِطَ القَصَبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He bound a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HurodiY~","text_ar":"حُرْدِىّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(q. v.)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon the fence of reeds,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"canes,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a fold for sheep &c.]       -A3-  Also, (K,) inf. n. as above, (T, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a man)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"betook himself,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"repaired, for covert,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lodging, to a"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"house,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hut, such as is called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kuwx","text_ar":"كُوخ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with a gibbous roof."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.)"}],"source_refs":["T","L","K","S"]},{"entry_id":"n7593","headword_ar":"حَرْدٌ","root":"Hrd","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaSodN","text_ar":"قَصْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": whence the phrase,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qado Haradotu","text_ar":"قَدْ حَرَدْتُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Harodaka","text_ar":"حَرْدَكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see 1.       -A2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Anger;"},{"kind":"text","text":"[as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaradN","text_ar":"حَرَدٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": see 1:] so in the prov.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tamas~ako biHarodika Hat~aY tudorika Haq~aka","text_ar":"تَمَسَّكْ بِحَرْدِكَ حَتَّى تُدْرِكَ حَقَّكَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Retain,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"persist in, thine anger until thou obtain thy right."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Rancour,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"enmity which one retains in the heart, watching for an opportunity to indulge it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(El-Kálee, MF.)       -A3-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HariydN","text_ar":"حَرِيدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n7594","headword_ar":"حِرْدٌ","root":"Hrd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"The"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maboEar","text_ar":"مَبْعَر"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e. the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"intestine,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"gut, containing the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baEor","text_ar":"بَعْر"},{"kind":"text","text":", or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dung,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] of a camel, (As, S, K,) male or female; (K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HirodapN","text_ar":"حِرْدَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (As, K:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HuruwdN","text_ar":"حُرُودٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (As, S.) ―         -b2-  An"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"intestine,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a gut:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T:) pl. as above: (IAar:) [or]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHoraAdN","text_ar":"اَحْرَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"intestines,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"guts,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of camels; and is probably a pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HirodN","text_ar":"حِرْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HuruwdN","text_ar":"حُرُودٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mabaAEir","text_ar":"مَبَاعِر"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amoEaA='","text_ar":"اَمْعَا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":"are nearly alike. (L.) Accord. to Lth [and the K],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HirodN","text_ar":"حِرْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A piece of a camel's hump:"},{"kind":"text","text":"but this is a mistake: it means (as explained above) an intestine, or a gut. (T.)"}],"source_refs":["As","S","K","T","IAar"]},{"entry_id":"n7595","headword_ar":"حَرَدٌ","root":"Hrd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HarodN","text_ar":"حَرْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".       -A2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain disease in the legs of camels,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"occasioning them, in walking,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"going, to shake their legs, and to beat the ground with them much:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain disease in their fore legs;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not in the hind legs; caused by the cord whereby the fore shank is sometimes bound up to the arm:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an aridity in the tendons,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sinews, of one of the fore legs, occasioned by that cord,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"when the animal is young and recently weaned,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in consequence of which he beats the ground with his fore legs,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,) or ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"strikes"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his breast"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"therewith"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in walking,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"going:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) the disease thus called is casual; [or generally so; (see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HurayodaA='u","text_ar":"حُرَيْدَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":";)] not natural. (T.) [See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Harida","text_ar":"حَرِدَ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]"}],"source_refs":["K","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n7596","headword_ar":"حَرِدٌ","root":"Hrd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HariydN","text_ar":"حَرِيدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":       -A2-  and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAridN","text_ar":"حَارِدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":       -A3-  and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHoradu","text_ar":"اَحْرَدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places.       -A4-  Also A rope"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"uneven in its strands."},{"kind":"text","text":"(AHn, TA.) A bow-string"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having one or more of the several portions of which"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by their being twisted together"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it is composed longer than others."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muHar~adN","text_ar":"مُحَرَّدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]       -A5-  A man"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in want,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"needy."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Yoo, on the authority of an Arab of the desert.)"}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}